The flavors smell so good as it cooks all day!!

Google “six sisters slow cooker maple and brown sugar pork” for the recipe or visit our website!

Head to our website to get the full recipe, and save this video for reference!

We LOVE Greek night. There are so many different flavors in Greek cuisine, from spicy, to savory, to fresh!  If you haven't tried Greek food yet, then these ground turkey greek tacos with Tzatziki are a great place to start! They are based off of a traditional Greek dish called Gyros, pronounced, "Yee-ro's", traditionally served with thinly sliced lamb and flatbread! For this recipe, we have switched out lamb for ground turkey, and topped it with a delicious tzatziki sauce.

We love to try new recipes and experience the occasional fancy, involved recipe with more than 6 ingredients (Yes,  we just called a recipe with more than 6 ingredients fancy, because sometimes, life really is like that) but all jokes aside, can we all agree on the fact that sometimes we just want a good old fashioned Pizza Bagel? Especially if it's a mini Pizza Bagel? Because we all know that mini foods are superior to boring regular size foods?  So glad we're all on the same page. 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “Mini Pizza Bagels Recipe".

Two forces-the instant pot and sandwich-combine today to create an ultra fast meal! What is faster and easier than a sandwhich made with the Instant Pot? These Instant Pot Chicken Caesar Sandwiches are an easy breezy dinner (or lunch) that you can pretty much plan on making over and over-one bite is all it takes, you'll be hooked for life! If you have an Instant Pot and 25 minutes then you are well on your way to this delicious sandwich. Tag someone who could use an easy dinner-one can never have too many easy dinner ideas! 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “EASY Instant Pot Chicken Caesar Sandwiches Recipe!" 

https://www.sixsistersstuff.com/recipe/instant-pot-chicken-caesar-sandwiches/

node.text:
We love pretty much anything made in a slow cooker, but this macaroni and cheese recipe is good enough to be listed with "slowcooker greatest hits", in our opinon. And unlike those recipes with 6 different kinds of cheese, this recipe comes together SO easily-perfect for those days when you desperately need a big bowl of mac and cheese-not a grocery trip. Try this out today, and you might just trade in your boxed mac and cheese forever for this version-it's happened before! 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “ Slow Cooker Macroni and Cheese Recipe". 

https://www.sixsistersstuff.com/recipe/slow-cooker-creamy-macaroni-and-cheese/
